It‚Äôs a photo that I wish didn‚Äôt exist but now that it does I want everyone to see it. What started as an opportunity to photograph a cute little sea horse turned into one of frustration and sadness as the incoming tide brought with it countless pieces of trash and sewage. This sea horse drifts long with the trash day in and day out as it rides the currents that flow along the Indonesian archipelago. This photo serves as an allegory for the current and future state of our oceans. What sort of future are we creating? How can your actions shape our planet?‚Ä®.‚Ä®thanks to @eyosexpeditions for getting me there and to @nhm_wpy and @sea_legacy for getting this photo in front of as many eyes as possible. As I come to my final show of the year, I want to say thank you to my band, crew, and the incredible people I have on team EG. After years of touring you have proven your dedication and talent once again. Your positivity and resilience as touring musicians and crew will forever keep me in awe and, as always, I am so grateful to have you on this journey. Summer has proven to me what true loyalty is, and I've come through with a stronger team than ever. Thank you for having unfaltering belief and sticking with me. I can only look forward to the new era with you all. To think about the things to come gives me overwhelming excitement! Big respect and love x #EG4 #Loyalty
